       I was recently told by my mechanic that regular 30W was the preferred

oil for the type 4 engines. Of course we are talking about the vanagons but,

he told me the synthetic just didn't do the job that was meant by regular 
oil. He said synthetic was "too clean."
     Of course I use synthetic in mine and the whole oil debate is like a 
presidential smear campaign but, I don't truly know enough about it. I've 
always heard that synthetic oils are usually best for older engines while 
the standard is best for newer/rebuilt ones.
   I've almost always had older (100+k) vehicles so I've always used 
synthetic motor oil. Whether it helps or not I have no idea. My bus still 
uses about half a quart (sometimes) between gas tanks. But, this is also 
cause I haven't had the time, nor cash cause I've been fixing other things 
all summer, to rebuild heads, valves, and replace pushrod tubes and seals.
    So, in all this, I think you'll hear all kinds of advice. I usually try 
to listen to someone who sounds very smart worthy and keep that one to make 
my own decision. Take all the knowledge you can get and then make a choice.

  Good luck!
  Carl
Port Townsend, WA
